<section xmlns="http://xml.house.gov/schemas/uslm/1.0" style="-uslm-lc:I80" id="idc3296d80-47c4-11f1-bf59-9680b1269b87" identifier="/us/usc/t38/s1975"><num value="1975">§ 1975.</num><heading> Jurisdiction of District Courts</heading><content>
<p style="-uslm-lc:I11" class="indent0">The district courts of the United States shall have original jurisdiction of any civil action or claim against the United States founded upon this subchapter.</p>
</content><sourceCredit id="idc3296d81-47c4-11f1-bf59-9680b1269b87">(Added <ref href="/us/pl/89/214/s1/a">Pub. L. 89–214, § 1(a)</ref>, <date date="1965-09-29">Sept. 29, 1965</date>, <ref href="/us/stat/79/885">79 Stat. 885</ref>, § 775; renumbered § 1975, <ref href="/us/pl/102/83/s5/a">Pub. L. 102–83, § 5(a)</ref>, <date date="1991-08-06">Aug. 6, 1991</date>, <ref href="/us/stat/105/406">105 Stat. 406</ref>.)</sourceCredit>
